- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper presents a new tool for automating the numerical solution of partial differential equations, which involves mathematical computations and algorithms. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper focuses on the numerical solution of partial differential equations using the finite element method, which is a topic within numerical analysis. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the application of the finite element method to scientific computing, which is a topic within computational engineering, finance, and science. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper mentions the optimization of inner loops and block matrix operations, which are relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the use of abstractions and separation of concerns to ease the incorporation of separate contributions from computer scientists, numerical analysts, and application specialists, which are relevant to software engineering.
